Test Case Examples:
Basic Search Behavior
The system should correctly identify whether a given bogie ID exists in the list using Linear Search.
Search Match Found
If the search key matches an element in the array, the system should stop searching and return a successful result.
Search Match Not Found
If the search key does not exist in the array, the system should traverse the entire list and return a not-found result.
First Element Match
If the search key matches the first element of the array, the search should terminate immediately.
Last Element Match
If the search key matches the last element of the array, the search should traverse the list until the final element and then return success.
